Lua-GD -- GD bindings for Lua
(c) 2004 Alexandre Erwin Ittner <aittner@netuno.com.br>


               --- CAUTION: FIRST ALPHA RELEASE ---


+ Introduction

Lua-GD is a library that provides access to the Thomas Boutell's
GD library from Lua. It's ALPHA software and it continues under
development. DON'T USE THIS RELEASE FOR ANYTHING EXCEPT TESTING!
THE API STILLS SUBJECT TO CHANGES. Future releases will be more
stable.


+ Naming convention

   * All functions are loaded on a single table called 'gd'.
   * Methods uses camelCase names and begins with lower case letters.
   * Constants uses upper case names, separated by underscores. 
   * All functions, except gd.create*, gd.copy*, gd.fontCache* and 
     gd.useFontConfig, can use the colon operator for a more object
     oriented access.


+ Documentation

There is no docs for now, but there are some lua scripts with examples.



